First Time iPhone User', 'review_text': "Coming from an android background of more than 13 years, I was skeptical about the iPhone. Considering the amount of tech that's available in the android space iPhone is definitely lacking in tech. However, after using the iPhone for the past few weeks, I do understand the appeal behind it.Face ID was interesting and the level of trust apps give to face ID is confidence inspiring. I still prefer the fingerprint unlock by Samsung over the face id tech. But that's just me. The cameras in simple pickup and shoot does the job and competes with the Pixel cameras head to head. The deciding factor is between the post processing for the phones.The build is amazing on the iPhone but the screen does feel a bit lacking in comparison to the s24 Ultras screen, even thought the screen is made by Samsung themselves.The one thing that impressed me about the iPhone was the battery life, the phone refuses to die on a normal work day and will last for a long while on an off day. Additionally, the software experience was a fresh change of pace for me and I am liking it. The way most of the apps work on the iPhone really does elevate the premium appeal of the device.  This phone really is interesting to use and feels worthy of its price, considering this is the first time I am purchasing the iPhone.

First Time iPhone User', 'review_text': "Coming from an android background of more than 13 years, I was skeptical about the iPhone. Considering the amount of tech that's available in the android space iPhone is definitely lacking in tech. However, after using the iPhone for the past few weeks, I do understand the appeal behind it.Face ID was interesting and the level of trust apps give to face ID is confidence inspiring. I still prefer the fingerprint unlock by Samsung over the face id tech. But that's just me. The cameras in simple pickup and shoot does the job and competes with the Pixel cameras head to head. The deciding factor is between the post processing for the phones.The build is amazing on the iPhone but the screen does feel a bit lacking in comparison to the s24 Ultras screen, even thought the screen is made by Samsung themselves.The one thing that impressed me about the iPhone was the battery life, the phone refuses to die on a normal work day and will last for a long while on an off day. Additionally, the software experience was a fresh change of pace for me and I am liking it. The way most of the apps work on the iPhone really does elevate the premium appeal of the device.  This phone really is interesting to use and feels worthy of its price, considering this is the first time I am purchasing the iPhone.
